    content: "Data loss is one of the most stressful experiences for computer users. Whether it is precious family photos, important work documents, or years of collected data, losing files can feel catastrophic. The good news is that in many cases, data recovery is possible.\n\n## Common Causes of Data Loss\n\n### Logical Failures (Software Issues)\n- Accidental deletion\n- Formatting errors\n- Corrupted partitions\n- Virus/malware damage\n- Operating system crashes\n\n**Recovery Success Rate: 90-95%**\n\n### Physical Failures (Hardware Issues)\n- Head crash in hard drives\n- Motor failure\n- PCB (circuit board) damage\n- Water/fire damage\n- Wear and tear\n\n**Recovery Success Rate: 60-85%**\n\n## Types of Data Recovery\n\n### DIY Recovery\n\nFor simple cases:\n- Check Recycle Bin/Trash\n- Use File History/Time Machine\n- Try free recovery software (Recuva, PhotoRec)\n- Check cloud backups\n\n### Professional Recovery\n\nSeek professional help when:\n- Drive is not detected by computer\n- Drive makes clicking/grinding noises\n- DIY software fails to recover data\n- Data is critically important\n- Drive has physical damage\n\n## Our Recovery Process\n\nAt Universal IT Solution, we follow a systematic approach:\n\n1. **Free Assessment**: We examine the drive and provide a recovery estimate\n2. **Clone Creation**: We work on a clone to prevent further damage\n3. **Recovery Attempt**: Using professional tools and clean room facilities\n4. **Data Verification**: We verify recovered files with you\n5. **Secure Delivery**: Data returned on new media with confidentiality guaranteed\n\n## Prevention is Better Than Cure\n\n### 3-2-1 Backup Strategy\n- Keep 3 copies of important data\n- Use 2 different storage types\n- Store 1 copy offsite or in cloud\n\n### Best Practices\n- Enable automatic cloud backup (OneDrive, Google Drive)\n- Use external drives for periodic backups\n- Do not ignore drive warning signs\n- Keep antivirus updated\n- Use UPS to prevent power-related damage\n\n## When to Act\n\nStop using the device immediately if:\n- You accidentally deleted files\n- Drive is making unusual noises\n- System shows SMART errors\n- Files are disappearing mysteriously\n\n**Continuing to use a failing drive can overwrite recoverable data and reduce recovery chances.**\n\n## Cost of Data Recovery\n\n- Logical recovery: Rs. 1,500 - 5,000\n- Physical recovery: Rs. 5,000 - 25,000+\n- Severe damage: Rs. 15,000 - 50,000+\n\nAt Universal IT Solution, we offer competitive pricing and a no data, no charge policy for many recovery cases. Contact us immediately if you have experienced data loss - every minute counts!",
