    id: 13,
    title: "Laptop Screen Replacement Cost Guide",
    slug: "laptop-screen-replacement-cost",
    excerpt: "A cracked or damaged screen does not mean you need a new laptop. Learn about screen replacement costs and options.",
    category: "Laptop Tips",
    readTime: "4 min",
    date: "2025-03-18",
    image: "/gallery-1.jpg",
    content: "A damaged laptop screen is one of the most common issues users face. Whether it is a crack from an accidental drop, dead pixels, or display flickering, a faulty screen can make your laptop unusable. The good news is that screen replacement is often more economical than buying a new laptop.\n\n## When to Replace Your Screen\n\n### Physical Damage\n- Cracked or shattered glass\n- Visible lines or black spots\n- Liquid damage showing as discoloration\n\n### Display Issues\n- Flickering screen\n- Backlight problems (very dim display)\n- Color distortion\n- Dead pixels (black or colored dots)\n\n### Touch Issues (Touchscreens)\n- Unresponsive touch\n- Ghost touches (random inputs)\n- Calibration problems\n\n## Factors Affecting Replacement Cost\n\n### 1. Screen Size\n- 11-12 inch: Generally cheaper\n- 13-14 inch: Mid-range pricing\n- 15-16 inch: Higher pricing\n- 17+ inch: Most expensive\n\n### 2. Screen Type\n- **Standard HD (1366x768)**: Most affordable\n- **Full HD (1920x1080)**: Moderate pricing\n- **4K UHD (3840x2160)**: Premium pricing\n- **OLED**: Highest pricing\n- **Touchscreen**: Adds 30-50% to cost\n\n### 3. Brand Availability\n- Common brands (HP, Dell, Lenovo): Readily available\n- Premium brands (Apple, Microsoft): Higher cost\n- Older/rare models: May need special ordering\n\n## Cost Breakdown\n\n### Budget Laptops\n- Screen replacement: Rs. 2,500 - 4,500\n- With touchscreen: Rs. 4,000 - 6,500\n\n### Mid-Range Laptops\n- Screen replacement: Rs. 3,500 - 7,000\n- With touchscreen: Rs. 5,500 - 10,000\n\n### Premium Laptops\n- MacBook screen: Rs. 8,000 - 25,000\n- Dell XPS: Rs. 6,000 - 15,000\n- ThinkPad: Rs. 4,000 - 12,000\n\n## The Replacement Process\n\nAt Universal IT Solution, screen replacement involves:\n1. Free diagnosis to confirm screen issue\n2. Ordering the correct replacement panel\n3. Careful disassembly of your laptop\n4. Precise installation of new screen\n5. Testing for dead pixels and color accuracy\n6. Warranty coverage (3-6 months)\n\nMost screen replacements are completed the same day if the part is in stock.\n\n## Warranty on Replacement Screens\n\nWe provide:\n- 3-month warranty on standard screens\n- 6-month warranty on premium/OLED screens\n- Dead pixel guarantee\n- Color accuracy verification\n\nDo not let a broken screen force you into buying a new laptop. Contact Universal IT Solution for affordable screen replacement services in Muzaffarpur.",
